Ask HN: Should I follow the herd and implement AI or
text:
Hey all, I'm currently building an OKR platform called Distilled atm and I'm trying to figure out a few things. I've been brainstorming a "Marketplace" that would host community driven OKR templates that are deployable with a single click to the app. This pros to this are:

- Network effects - Community - More focused OKRs

With all the hype around AI however, I'm wondering if we should implement some Chat GPT type features to allow people to develop their OKRs that way. I don't see many pros to this, but it might be a cool marketing gimmick. Some points I've considered:

- May be more seamless - Expensive - Not as community driven

The latest version of the Mac version of Docker cannot start opengauss normally
text:
The latest version of the mac version of docker cannot start opengauss normally. After installation, run for a period of time and then close the mirror, and then restart and report an error. After using persistence, the gsql link reports failed to connect Unknown: 5432

The following is the start command

docker run --name opengauss --privileged=true -d -e GS_PASSWORD=openGauss@123 -v /Users/superadmin/Desktop/opengauss:/var/lib/opengauss -u root -p 5432:5432 enmotech/opengauss:latest

Ask HN: Does anybody remember a post about optimizing load times at YouTube?
text:
I swear that this existed, but I can't find it anywhere. It was a engineering blogpost where the author (a YouTube employee) talked about optimizing page load times at YouTube, where the unexpected result was that average page load times actually went up because more people with bad internet connections started using YouTube.

I would love to cite this in a talk, but I can't find the dang thing anywhere. It's the perfect case study for one of my points, but I've completely failed at finding it.
